values: why does everything seem so far away.

This life is sickening.

Giving up isn't enough, everything you do dies in vain, time never stands in your favor, love is always looking for something better, hope is an unfriendly pass time, happiness never feels like it used to, loneliness cant stand you and I'm just stuck on the outside looking in. I understand why people kill themselves. I wish I could, I wish I had it in me. Unfortunately this world is nowhere as grim as the next would be. But I'd love to be the reason you couldn't sleep at night. Maybe then you'd understand what it feels like to be consumed by a plague. You've ruined everything.

I hope you find this, I hope you read this one day. 

You don't know the first thing about me. You're nothing like me, you can't comprehend the truth.  You can't comprehend the idea of family coming first over all things. You were sucker punched and you've lost you're ability to see things for what they really are. If there's one thing I've learned, never take things at face value. There is always more to the story, there is always a past we're still waste deep in. Regardless if we're running from it, running to it or lying idle. 

It really is amusing my friend, seeing you, caught up in your own ignorance, tangled in a web of lies. I'm sure in the end you may experience a fraction of what I've had to live with for a longer time then you could even stand. You think this is the roots of hate and  jealousy? Or envy? I don't waste my time with that petty shit. It's not my job to convince anyone, its not my job to make you believe. This isn't a game to me, this is my life and you're playing with fire.
I'm completely warn out, but yet....so amused.

I'd love to hear you say you're proud of me.
I'd love to hear you say I'm doing a great job
I'd love to hear you say you've been thinking about me
I'd love to hear you say I'm sorry

I'd love to hear your voice.

Did you know; A woman you are engaged to, Biblically, is already considered to be your wife? Cool huh?

I learned a lot today. It's amazing how people change when they think they're being pushed into a corner. The absence of self-awareness can be disgusting.

Someone needs to hold you accountable.



Getting tired, hating all I've known.
Holding on, like it's all I have.
Count me out, when it's clear that I, find it hard to say.
And you, find it hard to care.

It blows my mind how people take love for granted. The comfort, the passion, the excitement, the feeling that there is that one person who will always be there for you. I feel like my love hasn't ever been good enough, like I'm never good enough. I gave myself away completely and now I'm stuck feeling incomplete. The best feeling in the world is having the love you give, recognized, and returned. Love can take you anywhere, get you through anything and you'd never feel like you've wasted a second of your life. No regrets. Her eyes take me away.

To me, the worst feeling in the world, is not only having that love held back and kept away from you, but given to someone else who doesn't deserve it. Someone else who lied and manipulated and cheated his way into your lovers heart. It tears me apart from the inside out how she can't see through it.

I feel like I'm stuck out in the cold, screaming in the dark thinking to myself  "I know shes lost again." All I want to do is be the one who loves her, who tells her every things fine, cuz I have you. At today's end, everything I see, feel, believe and know is screaming against the cruelty of this situation.

These are the days of God.

I drove up to Orlando this past weekend to see Kira and Melody, and to pick up some of my stuff.
I had no sleep, but it was well worth it.

I don't like being so far away from everything that makes me happy.

I absolutely hate overdraft fees. Now imagine 7 of them all at once... Seriously, we're all just feeding the banks and that shit pisses me off. Some people out there are getting hella rich off of peoples mistakes and accidents. I wish I didn't have to bank at all. I just got off of work, and I'm still raged at the fact that I have 7 of them piled up, waiting for me, haunting me. My face is on fire because working in a 34 degree cooler and then walking out to 80 degree Florida temperatures + humidity isn't as fun as it sounds.) and I can't tell if it's from the temperature change or my bank. I'm beat. This picture makes me laugh.

So I've been down in Ft. Myers for about 2 weeks now. I really miss home, I miss my daughter, I miss my family, and I find myself really missing Melody. I'm tired of experiencing these coincidences that just bring me back. I know God has his plan, but sometimes I really wish I could see the end results. I guess that would be cheating, and would probably leave little room for faith to play a part in my life.

On the other hand, I've met some really awesome people down here, and it makes things a lot easier (with or without furniture.) Work is kicking me in the ass, but I'm enjoying the challenge it's given me. I can't wait to get paid on Friday, the lack of sustenance is screwing with my energy levels, ughhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhh.

I just got off work, and I'm going to find something to do.
Goodnight neverland



I can't believe she really thinks feelings don't come from your heart...

Ive been hurt once again. I sit here alone in my mind wondering how this could get any worse. When you love someone so much that leaving them to absolve you of any pain caused directly by them would seem better, in actuality, selfish on both hands.

I guess this is one of my first times actually wondering if I was better off. It just blows my mind how inconsiderate she can be. How hurtful she can be, but yet I've never felt more loved in my life by another person. I never really thought I'd be a victim of inconsideration to this extent, in a relationship with her. To feel so left out, forgotten about, unwanted. Maybe I'm just too dry for her. Too boring, too un-fulfilling. I would certainly hope that I'snt the case.

How exclusive is our relationship? I can't even answer that. I know what I want it to be, but im lacking the mutual feeling. When experience surpasses all of this, and things are too good to be true...Then you hit little bump that leads to a fork in the road, and say to yourself "This is such a little issue compare to all the other shit we've been through, how can this be this way?"

A million and one questions answered with excuses and infidelity. Such opposition. Its beyond me, it really is. I wish that this was just a little easier. I wish that this didn't hurt me so much. I wish I wasnt viewed as the opinionated one. Ive tried, and oddly enough I'm still trying. You really think I'm one to just say "I fold!" Eat me. I have a dad, hes worse.

I guess I'm second guessing myself. Will the things I strive for be reached? Ever? You could have asked me this question months ago, I could answer it. 

I just want this feeling of insentience to pass so I can put love back in its place, where it should be. Where it was.

Oh yeah, welcome back jack ;)

Christianity is the second of the Abrahamic faiths; it follows Judaism and is followed by Islam. It differs in its belief of Jesus, as not a prophet nor historical figure, but as God in human form. The Holy Trinity is the concept that God takes three forms: the Father, the Son (Jesus), and the Holy Ghost (sometimes called Holy Spirit). Jesus taught the idea of instead of seeking revenge, one should love his or her neighbors and enemies. Christians believe that Jesus died on the cross to save humankind and forgive people's sins.
